snippet.textDisplay: Machine Head's Catharsis. Machine Head had 3 amazing albums before Catharsis. The Blackening from 2007 is their best album. Unto the locust follows up almost just as good in 2011. 2014's Bloodstone and Diamonds is awesome! What happened?? Catharsis is an embarassment to get through. Some songs on this album are embarrassing to talk about. You don't even want to consider sometimes that the same band that made The Blackening, made Catharsis. The rap rock on catharsis makes Fred Durst look like a mastermind. The SJW theme and the rip off slipknot riffs start this album off as cringy and then you get to the song "Bastards" A song that sounds like it was written by a 12 year old and lyrics about a man who has nothing to do but pout, complain and cry about the 2016 election not going his way. Its just San Francisco dogma. This whole album is cringe on many different levels. The final track is a song is literally a slowed down atmospheric version of Bastards that goes on way too long. This album is over 70 mins and its painful to get through.

The rap rock on catharsis makes Fred Durst look like a mastermind. The SJW theme and the rip off slipknot riffs start this album off as cringy and then you get to the song "Bastards" A song that sounds like it was written by a 12 year old and lyrics about a man who has nothing to do but pout, complain and cry about the 2016 election not going his way. Its just San Francisco dogma. This whole album is cringe on many different levels. The final track is a song is literally a slowed down atmospheric version of Bastards that goes on way too long. This album is over 70 mins and its painful to get through.
